rob": 0.0008725219522602856}, {"id": 35, "seek": 15032, "start": 152.79999999999998, "end": 154.4, "text": " So this is the idea of the ring protection model.", "tokens": [50488, 407, 341, 307, 264, 1558, 295, 264, 4875, 6334, 2316, 13, 50568], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18254548105700263, "compression_ratio": 1.8385826771653544, "no_speech_prob": 0.0008725219522602856}, {"id": 36, "seek": 15032, "start": 154.4, "end": 158.6, "text": " You rate eight outwards at the center, ring zero is where you have the most trust.", "tokens": [50568, 509, 3314, 3180, 484, 2015, 412, 264, 3056, 11, 4875, 4018, 307, 689, 291, 362, 264, 881, 3361, 13, 50778], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18254548105700263, "compression_ratio": 1.8385826771653544, "no_speech_prob": 0.0008725219522602856}, {"id": 37, "seek": 15032, "start": 158.6, "end": 165.32, "text": " And you rate eight outwards to layer three, ring three where you have the least trust.", "tokens": [50778, 400, 291, 3314, 3180, 484, 2015, 281, 4583, 1045, 11, 4875, 1045, 689, 291, 362, 264, 1935, 3361, 13, 51114], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18254548105700263, "compression_ratio": 1.8385826771653544, "no_speech_prob": 0.0008725219522602856}, {"id": 38, "seek": 15032, "start": 165.32, "end": 169.88, "text": " Next, let's talk about the concept of secure memory management.", "tokens": [51114, 3087, 11, 718, 311, 751, 466, 264, 3410, 295, 7144, 4675, 4592, 13, 51342], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18254548105700263, "compression_ratio": 1.8385826771653544, "no_speech_prob": 0.0008725219522602856}, {"id": 39, "seek": 15032, "start": 169.88, "end": 174.56, "text": " And this is the idea that in a system, we'll have multiple programs running.", "tokens": [51342, 400, 341, 307, 264, 1558, 300, 294, 257, 1185, 11, 321, 603, 362, 3866, 4268, 2614, 13, 51576], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18254548105700263, "compression_ratio": 1.8385826771653544, "no_speech_prob": 0.0008725219522602856}, {"id": 40, "seek": 15032, "start": 174.56, "end": 179.64, "text": " And each of those programs will have some data loaded into volatile memory, RAM, random", "tokens": [51576, 400, 1184, 295, 729, 4268, 486, 362, 512, 1412, 13210, 666, 34377, 4675, 11, 14561, 11, 4974, 51830], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18254548105700263, "compression_ratio": 1.8385826771653544, "no_speech_prob": 0.0008725219522602856}, {"id": 41, "seek": 17964, "start": 179.64, "end": 181.6, "text": " access memory.", "tokens": [50364, 2105, 4675, 13, 50462], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1453436365667379, "compression_ratio": 1.8227848101265822, "no_speech_prob": 0.026235373690724373}, {"id": 42, "seek": 17964, "start": 181.6, "end": 185.95999999999998, "text": " And the idea behind secure memory management is that we want to make sure that if, if", "tokens": [50462, 400, 264, 1558, 2261, 7144, 4675, 4592, 307, 300, 321, 528, 281, 652, 988, 300, 498, 11, 498, 50680], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1453436365667379, "compression_ratio": 1.8227848101265822, "no_speech_prob": 0.026235373690724373}, {"id": 43, "seek": 17964, "start": 185.95999999999998, "end": 191.27999999999997, "text": " process A is accessing data in RAM, what data should be allowed to access?", "tokens": [50680, 1399, 316, 307, 26440, 1412, 294, 14561, 11, 437, 1412, 820, 312, 4350, 281, 2105, 30, 50946], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1453436365667379, "compression_ratio": 1.8227848101265822, "no_speech_prob": 0.026235373690724373}, {"id": 44, "seek": 17964, "start": 191.27999999999997, "end": 192.27999999999997, "text": " Only its own data.", "tokens": [50946, 5686, 1080, 1065, 1412, 13, 50996], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1453436365667379, "compression_ratio": 1.8227848101265822, "no_speech_prob": 0.026235373690724373}, {"id": 45, "seek": 17964, "start": 192.27999999999997, "end": 194.16, "text": " That's the idea of secure memory management.", "tokens": [50996, 663, 311, 264, 1558, 295, 7144, 4675, 4592, 13, 51090], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1453436365667379, "compression_ratio": 1.8227848101265822, "no_speech_prob": 0.026235373690724373}, {"id": 46, "seek": 17964, "start": 194.16, "end": 197.76, "text": " You allocate parts of memory to different processes.", "tokens": [51090, 509, 35713, 3166, 295, 4675, 281, 819, 7555, 13, 51270], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1453436365667379, "compression_ratio": 1.8227848101265822, "no_speech_prob": 0.026235373690724373}, {"id": 47, "seek": 17964, "start": 197.76, "end": 202.0, "text": " And then you have a component in place system that's controlling and making sure that only", "tokens": [51270, 400, 550, 291, 362, 257, 6542, 294, 1081, 1185, 300, 311, 14905, 293, 1455, 988, 300, 787, 51482], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1453436365667379, "compression_ratio": 1.8227848101265822, "no_speech_prob": 0.026235373690724373}, {"id": 48, "seek": 17964, "start": 202.0, "end": 206.23999999999998, "text": " process A can access process A's data in memory.", "tokens": [51482, 1399, 316, 393, 2105, 1399, 316, 311, 1412, 294, 4675, 13, 51694], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1453436365667379, "compression_ratio": 1.8227848101265822, "no_speech_prob": 0.026235373690724373}, {"id": 49, "seek": 20624, "start": 206.24, "end": 211.24, "text": " What do you think we would fundamentally call that system that's mediating that access?", "tokens": [50364, 708, 360, 291, 519, 321, 576, 17879, 818, 300, 1185, 300, 311, 17269, 990, 300, 2105, 30, 50614], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16976982939477062, "compression_ratio": 1.7411764705882353, "no_speech_prob": 0.0009542827028781176}, {"id": 50, "seek": 20624, "start": 211.24, "end": 213.04000000000002, "text": " That would be a security kernel.", "tokens": [50614, 663, 576, 312, 257, 3825, 28256, 13, 50704], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16976982939477062, "compression_ratio": 1.7411764705882353, "no_speech_prob": 0.0009542827028781176}, {"id": 51, "seek": 20624, "start": 213.04000000000002, "end": 217.84, "text": " So secure memory management is about essentially implementing a security kernel that controls", "tokens": [50704, 407, 7144, 4675, 4592, 307, 466, 4476, 18114, 257, 3825, 28256, 300, 9003, 50944], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16976982939477062, "compression_ratio": 1.7411764705882353, "no_speech_prob": 0.0009542827028781176}, {"id": 52, "seek": 20624, "start": 217.84, "end": 220.8, "text": " which processes can access, which data in RAM.", "tokens": [50944, 597, 7555, 393, 2105, 11, 597, 1412, 294, 14561, 13, 51092], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16976982939477062, "compression_ratio": 1.7411764705882353, "no_speech_prob": 0.0009542827028781176}, {"id": 53, "seek": 20624, "start": 220.8, "end": 225.76000000000002, "text": " And as you can see here in the diagram, process A can only access process A's data and not", "tokens": [51092, 400, 382, 291, 393, 536, 510, 294, 264, 10686, 11, 1399, 316, 393, 787, 2105, 1399, 316, 311, 1412, 293, 406, 51340], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16976982939477062, "compression_ratio": 1.7411764705882353, "no_speech_prob": 0.0009542827028781176}, {"id": 54, "seek": 20624, "start": 225.76000000000002, "end": 230.60000000000002, "text": " data from the operating system or other processes.", "tokens": [51340, 1412, 490, 264, 7447, 1185, 420, 661, 7555, 13, 51582], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16976982939477062, "compression_ratio": 1.7411764705882353, "no_speech_prob": 0.0009542827028781176}, {"id": 55, "seek": 20624, "start": 230.60000000000002, "end": 233.04000000000002, "text": " Next we have the concept of data hiding.", "tokens": [51582, 3087, 321, 362, 264, 3410, 295, 1412, 10596, 13, 51704], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16976982939477062, "compression_ratio": 1.7411764705882353, "no_speech_prob": 0.0009542827028781176}, {"id": 56, "seek": 23304, "start": 233.04, "end": 239.35999999999999, "text": " And this is the idea that we can have data at different levels of confidentiality or value.", "tokens": [50364, 400, 341, 307, 264, 1558, 300, 321, 393, 362, 1412, 412, 819, 4358, 295, 27054, 507, 420, 2158, 13, 50680], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16087931210232764, "compression_ratio": 1.823008849557522, "no_speech_prob": 0.003178355284035206}, {"id": 57, "seek": 23304, "start": 239.35999999999999, "end": 244.28, "text": " And the idea behind data hiding is that if you are at a lower level of confidentiality,", "tokens": [50680, 400, 264, 1558, 2261, 1412, 10596, 307, 300, 498, 291, 366, 412, 257, 3126, 1496, 295, 27054, 507, 11, 50926], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16087931210232764, "compression_ratio": 1.823008849557522, "no_speech_prob": 0.003178355284035206}, {"id": 58, "seek": 23304, "start": 244.28, "end": 246.84, "text": " then you cannot see data at higher levels.", "tokens": [50926, 550, 291, 2644, 536, 1412, 412, 2946, 4358, 13, 51054], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16087931210232764, "compression_ratio": 1.823008849557522, "no_speech_prob": 0.003178355284035206}, {"id": 59, "seek": 23304, "start": 246.84, "end": 249.28, "text": " That data is hidden from you.", "tokens": [51054, 663, 1412, 307, 7633, 490, 291, 13, 51176], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16087931210232764, "compression_ratio": 1.823008849557522, "no_speech_prob": 0.003178355284035206}, {"id": 60, "seek": 23304, "start": 249.28, "end": 254.68, "text": " And so data hiding is basically just an implementation of which model that John talked about.", "tokens": [51176, 400, 370, 1412, 10596, 307, 1936, 445, 364, 11420, 295, 597, 2316, 300, 2619, 2825, 466, 13, 51446], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16087931210232764, "compression_ratio": 1.823008849557522, "no_speech_prob": 0.003178355284035206}, {"id": 61, "seek": 23304, "start": 254.68, "end": 259.68, "text": " Which model had to do with confidential data at different layers?", "tokens": [51446, 3013, 2316, 632, 281, 360, 365, 27054, 1412, 412, 819, 7914, 30, 51696], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16087931210232764, "compression_ratio": 1.823008849557522, "no_speech_prob": 0.003178355284035206}, {"id": 62, "seek": 25968, "start": 260.68, "end": 264.2, "text": " And so Bella Padula is essentially what data hiding is all about.", "tokens": [50414, 400, 370, 29133, 18691, 3780, 307, 4476, 437, 1412, 10596, 307, 439, 466, 13, 50590], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18557618015496305, "compression_ratio": 1.8052805280528053, "no_speech_prob": 0.10113828629255295}, {"id": 63, "seek": 25968, "start": 264.2, "end": 270.52, "text": " If you're down at a lower level of secrecy, you can't see data at higher levels of secrecy.", "tokens": [50590, 759, 291, 434, 760, 412, 257, 3126, 1496, 295, 34432, 1344, 11, 291, 393, 380, 536, 1412, 412, 2946, 4358, 295, 34432, 1344, 13, 50906], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18557618015496305, "compression_ratio": 1.8052805280528053, "no_speech_prob": 0.10113828629255295}, {"id": 64, "seek": 25968, "start": 270.52, "end": 275.08, "text": " The last piece we'll talk about in this section is what is known as code signing and validation.", "tokens": [50906, 440, 1036, 2522, 321, 603, 751, 466, 294, 341, 3541, 307, 437, 307, 2570, 382, 3089, 13393, 293, 24071, 13, 51134], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18557618015496305, "compression_ratio": 1.8052805280528053, "no_speech_prob": 0.10113828629255295}, {"id": 65, "seek": 25968, "start": 275.08, "end": 279.12, "text": " And this actually relies on a lot of cryptographic technologies and techniques that we haven't", "tokens": [51134, 400, 341, 767, 30910, 322, 257, 688, 295, 9844, 12295, 7943, 293, 7512, 300, 321, 2378, 380, 51336], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18557618015496305, "compression_ratio": 1.8052805280528053, "no_speech_prob": 0.10113828629255295}, {"id": 66, "seek": 25968, "start": 279.12, "end": 282.2, "text": " talked about yet like hashing and digital signatures and so forth.", "tokens": [51336, 2825, 466, 1939, 411, 575, 571, 293, 4562, 32322, 293, 370, 5220, 13, 51490], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18557618015496305, "compression_ratio": 1.8052805280528053, "no_speech_prob": 0.10113828629255295}, {"id": 67, "seek": 25968, "start": 282.2, "end": 285.64, "text": " So don't worry about the technical pieces of how this actually works.", "tokens": [51490, 407, 500, 380, 3292, 466, 264, 6191, 3755, 295, 577, 341, 767, 1985, 13, 51662], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18557618015496305, "compression_ratio": 1.8052805280528053, "no_speech_prob": 0.10113828629255295}, {"id": 68, "seek": 25968, "start": 285.64, "end": 288.64, "text": " Just understand what we use code signing and validation for.", "tokens": [51662, 1449, 1223, 437, 321, 764, 3089, 13393, 293, 24071, 337, 13, 51812], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18557618015496305, "compression_ratio": 1.8052805280528053, "no_speech_prob": 0.10113828629255295}, {"id": 69, "seek": 28864, "start": 288.64, "end": 292.8, "text": " And later on, we'll explain how this actually gets done.", "tokens": [50364, 400, 1780, 322, 11, 321, 603, 2903, 577, 341, 767, 2170, 1096, 13, 50572], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15665214538574218, "compression_ratio": 1.8885135135135136, "no_speech_prob": 0.00619910005480051}, {"id": 70, "seek": 28864, "start": 292.8, "end": 295.2, "text": " So here's what you use code signing and validation for.", "tokens": [50572, 407, 510, 311, 437, 291, 764, 3089, 13393, 293, 24071, 337, 13, 50692], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15665214538574218, "compression_ratio": 1.8885135135135136, "no_speech_prob": 0.00619910005480051}, {"id": 71, "seek": 28864, "start": 295.2, "end": 299.08, "text": " And let me use a modern phone, something like an iPhone as an example.", "tokens": [50692, 400, 718, 385, 764, 257, 4363, 2593, 11, 746, 411, 364, 7252, 382, 364, 1365, 13, 50886], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15665214538574218, "compression_ratio": 1.8885135135135136, "no_speech_prob": 0.00619910005480051}, {"id": 72, "seek": 28864, "start": 299.08, "end": 301.32, "text": " So we've all got phones, something like this.", "tokens": [50886, 407, 321, 600, 439, 658, 10216, 11, 746, 411, 341, 13, 50998], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15665214538574218, "compression_ratio": 1.8885135135135136, "no_speech_prob": 0.00619910005480051}, {"id": 73, "seek": 28864, "start": 301.32, "end": 305.52, "text": " And you probably notice that every so often you get a little nudge from Apple saying,", "tokens": [50998, 400, 291, 1391, 3449, 300, 633, 370, 2049, 291, 483, 257, 707, 297, 16032, 490, 6373, 1566, 11, 51208], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15665214538574218, "compression_ratio": 1.8885135135135136, "no_speech_prob": 0.00619910005480051}, {"id": 74, "seek": 28864, "start": 305.52, "end": 307.0, "text": " hey, you need to update your device.", "tokens": [51208, 4177, 11, 291, 643, 281, 5623, 428, 4302, 13, 51282], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15665214538574218, "compression_ratio": 1.8885135135135136, "no_speech_prob": 0.00619910005480051}, {"id": 75, "seek": 28864, "start": 307.0, "end": 312.24, "text": " Hey, hey, and what you're going to go and do is you're going to go into system settings", "tokens": [51282, 1911, 11, 4177, 11, 293, 437, 291, 434, 516, 281, 352, 293, 360, 307, 291, 434, 516, 281, 352, 666, 1185, 6257, 51544], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15665214538574218, "compression_ratio": 1.8885135135135136, "no_speech_prob": 0.00619910005480051}, {"id": 76, "seek": 28864, "start": 312.24, "end": 314.91999999999996, "text": " and you're going to say, update my device.", "tokens": [51544, 293, 291, 434, 516, 281, 584, 11, 5623, 452, 4302, 13, 51678], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15665214538574218, "compression_ratio": 1.8885135135135136, "no_speech_prob": 0.00619910005480051}, {"id": 77, "seek": 28864, "start": 314.91999999999996, "end": 317.56, "text": " And when you've done this, you probably notice that when you say, you know,", "tokens": [51678, 400, 562, 291, 600, 1096, 341, 11, 291, 1391, 3449, 300, 562, 291, 584, 11, 291, 458, 11, 51810], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15665214538574218, "compression_ratio": 1.8885135135135136, "no_speech_prob": 0.00619910005480051}, {"id": 78, "seek": 31756, "start": 317.56, "end": 320.52, "text": " you finally go through all the, you know, all the click wrap agreements and accept all", "tokens": [50364, 291, 2721, 352, 807, 439, 264, 11, 291, 458, 11, 439, 264, 2052, 7019, 21422, 293, 3241, 439, 50512], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17226577266570062, "compression_ratio": 1.9489489489489489, "no_speech_prob": 0.004224860575050116}, {"id": 79, "seek": 31756, "start": 320.52, "end": 323.72, "text": " the terms and conditions and everything and you finally say, yeah, install the update.", "tokens": [50512, 264, 2115, 293, 4487, 293, 1203, 293, 291, 2721, 584, 11, 1338, 11, 3625, 264, 5623, 13, 50672], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17226577266570062, "compression_ratio": 1.9489489489489489, "no_speech_prob": 0.004224860575050116}, {"id": 80, "seek": 31756, "start": 323.72, "end": 328.32, "text": " It doesn't just install instantly for the first little while it says downloading.", "tokens": [50672, 467, 1177, 380, 445, 3625, 13518, 337, 264, 700, 707, 1339, 309, 1619, 32529, 13, 50902], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17226577266570062, "compression_ratio": 1.9489489489489489, "no_speech_prob": 0.004224860575050116}, {"id": 81, "seek": 31756, "start": 328.32, "end": 332.44, "text": " But then when it's done downloading, it doesn't again just install instantly instead.", "tokens": [50902, 583, 550, 562, 309, 311, 1096, 32529, 11, 309, 1177, 380, 797, 445, 3625, 13518, 2602, 13, 51108], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17226577266570062, "compression_ratio": 1.9489489489489489, "no_speech_prob": 0.004224860575050116}, {"id": 82, "seek": 31756, "start": 332.44, "end": 333.44, "text": " What does it say?", "tokens": [51108, 708, 775, 309, 584, 30, 51158], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17226577266570062, "compression_ratio": 1.9489489489489489, "no_speech_prob": 0.004224860575050116}, {"id": 83, "seek": 31756, "start": 333.44, "end": 336.28, "text": " So if it took like 10 minutes to download, then usually for like the next 10 minutes,", "tokens": [51158, 407, 498, 309, 1890, 411, 1266, 2077, 281, 5484, 11, 550, 2673, 337, 411, 264, 958, 1266, 2077, 11, 51300], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17226577266570062, "compression_ratio": 1.9489489489489489, "no_speech_prob": 0.004224860575050116}, {"id": 84, "seek": 31756, "start": 336.28, "end": 337.76, "text": " what does it say?", "tokens": [51300, 437, 775, 309, 584, 30, 51374], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17226577266570062, "compression_ratio": 1.9489489489489489, "no_speech_prob": 0.004224860575050116}, {"id": 85, "seek": 31756, "start": 337.76, "end": 338.76, "text": " Verifying.", "tokens": [51374, 4281, 5489, 13, 51424], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17226577266570062, "compression_ratio": 1.9489489489489489, "no_speech_prob": 0.004224860575050116}, {"id": 86, "seek": 31756, "start": 338.76, "end": 343.64, "text": " Now, there's something really cool happening behind the scenes when it says verifying.", "tokens": [51424, 823, 11, 456, 311, 746, 534, 1627, 2737, 2261, 264, 8026, 562, 309, 1619, 1306, 5489, 13, 51668], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17226577266570062, "compression_ratio": 1.9489489489489489, "no_speech_prob": 0.004224860575050116}, {"id": 87, "seek": 31756, "start": 343.64, "end": 346.92, "text": " What your phone is actually doing is it's making sure that that software update that it", "tokens": [51668, 708, 428, 2593, 307, 767, 884, 307, 309, 311, 1455, 988, 300, 300, 4722, 5623, 300, 309, 51832], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17226577266570062, "compression_ratio": 1.9489489489489489, "no_speech_prob": 0.004224860575050116}, {"id": 88, "seek": 34692, "start": 346.92, "end": 352.52000000000004, "text": " just downloaded actually came from Apple because if you're downloading an update to your", "tokens": [50364, 445, 21748, 767, 1361, 490, 6373, 570, 498, 291, 434, 32529, 364, 5623, 281, 428, 50644], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10729544812982733, "compression_ratio": 1.975177304964539, "no_speech_prob": 0.003694954328238964}, {"id": 89, "seek": 34692, "start": 352.52000000000004, "end": 355.44, "text": " phone that's going to make a whole bunch of changes to your operating system, you want", "tokens": [50644, 2593, 300, 311, 516, 281, 652, 257, 1379, 3840, 295, 2962, 281, 428, 7447, 1185, 11, 291, 528, 50790], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10729544812982733, "compression_ratio": 1.975177304964539, "no_speech_prob": 0.003694954328238964}, {"id": 90, "seek": 34692, "start": 355.44, "end": 358.0, "text": " to make darn sure that actually came from a trusted source.", "tokens": [50790, 281, 652, 29063, 988, 300, 767, 1361, 490, 257, 16034, 4009, 13, 50918], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10729544812982733, "compression_ratio": 1.975177304964539, "no_speech_prob": 0.003694954328238964}, {"id": 91, "seek": 34692, "start": 358.0, "end": 361.56, "text": " And so if it's an Apple phone, you want to make sure it came from Apple.", "tokens": [50918, 400, 370, 498, 309, 311, 364, 6373, 2593, 11, 291, 528, 281, 652, 988, 309, 1361, 490, 6373, 13, 51096], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10729544812982733, "compression_ratio": 1.975177304964539, "no_speech_prob": 0.003694954328238964}, {"id": 92, "seek": 34692, "start": 361.56, "end": 365.56, "text": " So the first thing that code signing validation is all about is the authenticity.", "tokens": [51096, 407, 264, 700, 551, 300, 3089, 13393, 24071, 307, 439, 466, 307, 264, 34215, 13, 51296], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10729544812982733, "compression_ratio": 1.975177304964539, "no_speech_prob": 0.003694954328238964}, {"id": 93, "seek": 34692, "start": 365.56, "end": 368.8, "text": " You know who the update came from.", "tokens": [51296, 509, 458, 567, 264, 5623, 1361, 490, 13, 51458], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10729544812982733, "compression_ratio": 1.975177304964539, "no_speech_prob": 0.003694954328238964}, {"id": 94, "seek": 34692, "start": 368.8, "end": 371.56, "text": " And the next piece is integrity.", "tokens": [51458, 400, 264, 958, 2522, 307, 16000, 13, 51596], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10729544812982733, "compression_ratio": 1.975177304964539, "no_speech_prob": 0.003694954328238964}, {"id": 95, "seek": 34692, "start": 371.56, "end": 376.44, "text": " If you've downloaded all this code from Apple, you want to make sure that none of the instructions", "tokens": [51596, 759, 291, 600, 21748, 439, 341, 3089, 490, 6373, 11, 291, 528, 281, 652, 988, 300, 6022, 295, 264, 9415, 51840], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10729544812982733, "compression_ratio": 1.975177304964539, "no_speech_prob": 0.003694954328238964}, {"id": 96, "seek": 37644, "start": 376.44, "end": 379.08, "text": " have gotten scrambled, none of the pieces are missing.", "tokens": [50364, 362, 5768, 49127, 11, 6022, 295, 264, 3755, 366, 5361, 13, 50496], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10871816272577964, "compression_ratio": 1.8402777777777777, "no_speech_prob": 0.00040665679262019694}, {"id": 97, "seek": 37644, "start": 379.08, "end": 384.8, "text": " You want to make sure that that whole software update is complete, has integrity.", "tokens": [50496, 509, 528, 281, 652, 988, 300, 300, 1379, 4722, 5623, 307, 3566, 11, 575, 16000, 13, 50782], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10871816272577964, "compression_ratio": 1.8402777777777777, "no_speech_prob": 0.00040665679262019694}, {"id": 98, "seek": 37644, "start": 384.8, "end": 389.84, "text": " And so that's the two major pieces of functionality that code signing provides.", "tokens": [50782, 400, 370, 300, 311, 264, 732, 2563, 3755, 295, 14980, 300, 3089, 13393, 6417, 13, 51034], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10871816272577964, "compression_ratio": 1.8402777777777777, "no_speech_prob": 0.00040665679262019694}, {"id": 99, "seek": 37644, "start": 389.84, "end": 393.36, "text": " It allows you to know where a software update came from.", "tokens": [51034, 467, 4045, 291, 281, 458, 689, 257, 4722, 5623, 1361, 490, 13, 51210], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10871816272577964, "compression_ratio": 1.8402777777777777, "no_speech_prob": 0.00040665679262019694}, {"id": 100, "seek": 37644, "start": 393.36, "end": 398.48, "text": " And make sure that that software update has integrity, so authenticity and integrity.", "tokens": [51210, 400, 652, 988, 300, 300, 4722, 5623, 575, 16000, 11, 370, 34215, 293, 16000, 13, 51466], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10871816272577964, "compression_ratio": 1.8402777777777777, "no_speech_prob": 0.00040665679262019694}, {"id": 101, "seek": 37644, "start": 398.48, "end": 402.4, "text": " And the way that we achieve this is by creating what are known as digital signatures.", "tokens": [51466, 400, 264, 636, 300, 321, 4584, 341, 307, 538, 4084, 437, 366, 2570, 382, 4562, 32322, 13, 51662], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10871816272577964, "compression_ratio": 1.8402777777777777, "no_speech_prob": 0.00040665679262019694}, {"id": 102, "seek": 37644, "start": 402.4, "end": 405.32, "text": " And here's the stuff that we'll talk about in a lot more detail in the cryptographic", "tokens": [51662, 400, 510, 311, 264, 1507, 300, 321, 603, 751, 466, 294, 257, 688, 544, 2607, 294, 264, 9844, 12295, 51808], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10871816272577964, "compression_ratio": 1.8402777777777777, "no_speech_prob": 0.00040665679262019694}, {"id": 103, "seek": 40532, "start": 405.32, "end": 406.71999999999997, "text": " section, section.", "tokens": [50364, 3541, 11, 3541, 13, 50434], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2572508788690334, "compression_ratio": 1.675257731958763, "no_speech_prob": 0.02789893187582493}, {"id": 104, "seek": 40532, "start": 406.71999999999997, "end": 412.88, "text": " But you take your code, you hash that code, producing a fixed linked message digest, the", "tokens": [50434, 583, 291, 747, 428, 3089, 11, 291, 22019, 300, 3089, 11, 10501, 257, 6806, 9408, 3636, 13884, 11, 264, 50742], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2572508788690334, "compression_ratio": 1.675257731958763, "no_speech_prob": 0.02789893187582493}, {"id": 105, "seek": 40532, "start": 412.88, "end": 418.0, "text": " author of the software, then encrypts that digest with their private key, creating what", "tokens": [50742, 3793, 295, 264, 4722, 11, 550, 17972, 39280, 300, 13884, 365, 641, 4551, 2141, 11, 4084, 437, 50998], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2572508788690334, "compression_ratio": 1.675257731958763, "no_speech_prob": 0.02789893187582493}, {"id": 106, "seek": 40532, "start": 418.0, "end": 420.64, "text": " is known as a digital signature.", "tokens": [50998, 307, 2570, 382, 257, 4562, 13397, 13, 51130], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2572508788690334, "compression_ratio": 1.675257731958763, "no_speech_prob": 0.02789893187582493}, {"id": 107, "seek": 40532, "start": 420.64, "end": 423.84, "text": " That's how you sign code, you create a digital signature.", "tokens": [51130, 663, 311, 577, 291, 1465, 3089, 11, 291, 1884, 257, 4562, 13397, 13, 51290], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2572508788690334, "compression_ratio": 1.675257731958763, "no_speech_prob": 0.02789893187582493}, {"id": 108, "seek": 40532, "start": 423.84, "end": 426.64, "text": " So that's the idea behind code signing.", "tokens": [51290, 407, 300, 311, 264, 1558, 2261, 3089, 13393, 13, 51430], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2572508788690334, "compression_ratio": 1.675257731958763, "no_speech_prob": 0.02789893187582493}], "language": "en"}